  "texts": [
    "He explains the difference between Generative models and discriminative models: generative models generate/create new data instances that are similar to the data they were trained on, whereas discriminative models discriminate/distinguish between different data classes/categories.For example, generative models are like artists that have been trained in certain painting styles (e.g., Impressionism), and discriminative models are like art critics.",
    "Trained Gen AI models (like artists) would be able to create a new painting in the Impressionist style, whereas discriminative models (like art critics) would be able to tell whether a painting is Impressionist or not, but unable to create new paintings on their own.",
    "Development of modern Generative AI models: ChatGPTArtificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) have been around since the mid-1950s.",
    "Despite continuous development of AI and ML models referenced above, there were very few tangible results until 2010.",
    "After that we have seen breakthroughs in the development of AI models in tandem with deep learning neural networks, greatly improved computing power, a huge expansion in learning databases facilitated by growing digital economy, and significantly better programs/algorithms."
